        },
        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "A rare genetic developmental defect during embryogenesis syndrome characterized by total or partial colonic aganglionosis associated with peripheral usually multifocal neuroblastic tumors (ganglioneuroblastoma neuroblastoma ganglioneuroma). Congenital central hypoventilation syndrome with variable severity of respiratory compromise cardiovascular and ophthalmologic symptoms consistent with autonomic nervous system dysfunction is occasionally associated."
        },
